    <fr:title text="Delicious numbing vinegar sauce">Delicious numbing vinegar sauce</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Recipe</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>This sauce can be served over rice, noodles, dumplings, or fish.</fr:p>
    <fr:ol><fr:li>Take some Szechuan peppercorns and dried chili flakes (or dried chilis that you have shattered) and crush them lightly in a mortar and pestle.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Toast the peppercorns and chili lightly in a hot pan.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Fry the peppercorns and chili in plenty of oil.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Fry some thinly chopped garlic without burning it.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Mix all this together (including the oil), and mix in some salt, mirin, rice vinegar, and (optionally) a very small amount of black vineger, to taste. Feel free to add more oil if needed.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Finely chop some coriander and mix it into the sauce.</fr:li></fr:ol>
  </fr:mainmatter>
